(29, 10, 11, 'What is Anxiety', 'Proceed.Fit', 'uploads/ANXIETY_cover.png', '', '<p>Have you ever heard the phrase \"Anxiety is the enemy\"? &nbsp;Well That isn\'t always the case though. &nbsp;<br>&nbsp;Every person\'s experience of stress and anxiety can be extremely different.&nbsp;<br>It can be beneficial to feel a bit sweaty and more alert before a major presentation or problem-solving at work.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/EQLSsYgnSAM\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe> <br><a title=\"Subscribe now to get the latest health-related information on our youtube channel.\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/proceedfit\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Subscribe now to get the latest health-related information on our youtube channel.</em></a></p>\r\n<h2>Here\'s everything you need to know about Anxiety. &nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>Anxiety is a mental state in, &nbsp;which a person feels a variety of emotions at once, &nbsp;including trepidation, &nbsp;fear, &nbsp;unease, &nbsp;and concern, &nbsp;to name a few. &nbsp;<br>Physical symptoms including palpitations, &nbsp;headaches, &nbsp;upset stomach, &nbsp;chest discomfort, &nbsp;and similar ones are present along with this. &nbsp;<br>Numerous factors, &nbsp;including a person\'s environment, &nbsp;specific traumatic events, &nbsp;or anything the individual perceives as painful, &nbsp;might set this off.&nbsp;<br>When this anxiety lasts for a long time, &nbsp;it\'s necessary to take professional help. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A lot of people struggle with anxiety disorders, &nbsp;especially in today\'s society of constant stress. &nbsp;But the greater concern is that we mostly don\'t consider it as a problem. &nbsp;The majority of people who have anxiety disorders and those close to them frequently mistake it for simple mood swings and personality traits. However, &nbsp;it is important to remember that the symptoms should not be disregarded because prompt treatment can totally heal the patient.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Factors and causes of anxiety</h2>\r\n<p>There are several elements that are known to affect the severity. &nbsp;Anxiety cannot be caused by a single factor. &nbsp;The causes of anxiety cases frequently interact with one another or work in unison.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>The following are contributing elements of anxiety disorders:</p>\r\n<p><br>&nbsp;<strong>1. Personality traits</strong><br>&nbsp;People who have anxiety problems constantly isolate themselves from other people because they see society as a dangerous place. &nbsp;The majority of people who suffer from severe anxiety have weak coping mechanisms and low self-esteem.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>2. Environment</strong><br>&nbsp;The environment also plays a role in the development of anxiety problems, &nbsp;a fact that many people are unaware of. &nbsp;A split from loved ones, &nbsp;financial difficulties, &nbsp;or other personal challenges concerning job or family life are examples of these situations.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>3. Brain complexity</strong><br>&nbsp;According to studies, &nbsp;certain imbalances and anomalies in a person\'s brain chemistry increase their risk of developing anxiety disorders. &nbsp;The majority of anxiety drugs on the market now aim to correct these chemical imbalances within the brain.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>&nbsp;4. Traumatic experiences</strong><br>&nbsp;Traumatic life events are also known to contribute to the development of anxiety. &nbsp;Traumatic life experiences include things like divorce, &nbsp;abuse, &nbsp;and death of a loved one. &nbsp;An individual might suffer great harm and depression as a result of traumatic events, &nbsp;which can lead to the emergence of anxiety disorders.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>5. Hereditary</strong><br>&nbsp;According to studies, &nbsp;anxiety problems are inherited. &nbsp;People with severe anxiety problems frequently have a history of mood disorders, &nbsp;drug misuse, &nbsp;and anxiety disorders. &nbsp;Anxiety problems are typically found in those who are also inherently sensitive to stress.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Let\'s now talk about some of the harmful physical effects that persistent anxiety may have. &nbsp;For instance, &nbsp;it might result in headaches, &nbsp;respiratory problems or shallow breathing, &nbsp;elevated blood pressure, &nbsp;idiopathic aches and pains, &nbsp;and overall fatigue. &nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>Memory loss has also been related to chronic stress, &nbsp;particularly when it comes to short-term and spatial memory.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Insomnia :&nbsp;</strong> &nbsp;When you are always anxious, &nbsp;your mind is likely to be racing, &nbsp;keeping you up and unable to fall asleep. &nbsp;Your stress hormones are frequently amplified by anxiety, &nbsp;keeping your brain busy and wired even when you don\'t actually need to or want to be.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In order to achieve improved emotional well-being, &nbsp;there are several ways you might be capable of overcoming anxiety. &nbsp;You might try implementing the following strategies with the advice of your doctor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>1)Nutrition</strong></h3>\r\n<p>According to research, &nbsp;the kind of meals and beverages you eat might affect your anxiety levels. &nbsp;According to one study, &nbsp;participants who drank more added sugar and saturated fat had higher levels of anxiety compared to those who consumed less of both.&nbsp;<br>Eating a diet high in fibre, &nbsp;fruits, &nbsp;veggies, &nbsp;and healthy fats, &nbsp;and low in processed foods is linked to better mood and easier management of mental illnesses including anxiety and depression. &nbsp;<br>Additionally, &nbsp;caffeine might make you feel more anxious. &nbsp; &nbsp;If you consume more than a single cup of coffee each day, &nbsp;consider reducing your intake or quitting entirely and see whether your anxiety decreases. &nbsp;Because there is caffeine in many teas, &nbsp;drinks, &nbsp;and foods (including chocolate), &nbsp;it\'s important to check nutrition labels and keep track of how much you\'re taking in.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>2) Physical Exercise</strong></p>\r\n<p>Find a method to exercise that feels good for you; it really doesn\'t have to be an exhausting, &nbsp;protracted workout. &nbsp;Even a little 10-minute walk may lift your spirits.&nbsp;<br>Exercise can help you focus better, &nbsp;sleep better, &nbsp;and feel less stressed. &nbsp;For patients with anxiety and depression, &nbsp;many doctors recommend physical activity in addition to counselling and/or medicine.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>3)Mindfulness</strong></h3>\r\n<p>You can also try practising mindfulness, &nbsp;meditating, &nbsp;breathing deeply, &nbsp;and progressive relaxation of muscles as additional coping mechanisms to assist reduce anxiety. &nbsp;According to one study, &nbsp;those who used the mindfulness meditation approach significantly reduced their levels of stress and anxiety.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>4)Be In Touch With Nature</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Another method to reduce anxiety is to get in touch with nature. &nbsp;Going for a walk in the park or even just listening to nature noises might help you feel more connected to nature and improve your mood, &nbsp;according to studies. &nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Treatment</h2>\r\n<p>Along with other diseases including phobias, &nbsp;anxiety attacks, &nbsp;and social phobia may also be a sign of generalised anxiety disorder.&nbsp;<br>It\'s critical to understand that you\'re not alone: More than 30% of individuals may have an anxiety problem at some time in their life, &nbsp;making anxiety disorders one of the most prevalent mental health diseases.&nbsp;<br>It\'s critical to get treatment if anxiety is upsetting you or interfering with your daily activities. &nbsp;Typically, &nbsp;psychotherapy, &nbsp;medicine, &nbsp;or a mix of the two are used as anxiety treatments. &nbsp;Discussing your symptoms with your doctor will help you identify the best course of therapy for you.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Natural Supplements</strong><br>You could get relief from stress or anxiety with a natural supplement. &nbsp;You can consider herbal medicine like Amoryn or making small dietary adjustments. &nbsp;Studies using Amoryn, &nbsp; have demonstrated excellent outcomes for 90% of patients with depression and 88.6% of patients with anxiety. &nbsp;The innate ability for pleasure in the brain is increased by the natural antidepressant amoryn.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>Another all-natural substance that reduces anxiety and panic episodes is seredyn, &nbsp;which also helps you feel calm and in control throughout the day.&nbsp;<br>These natural supplements frequently yield fruitful outcomes in a little amount of time and are typically not habit-forming. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It might be challenging to come out of a vicious cycle caused by anxiety. &nbsp;Luckily, &nbsp;anxiety is easy to cure. &nbsp;Self-help techniques for overcoming anxiety can be beneficial, &nbsp;but it\'s also crucial to discuss your treatment choices with your doctor. &nbsp;You may keep in mind that your anxiety isn\'t preventing you from fulfilling your goals by taking action to improve.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Note : The information provided here is for general informational purposes only and is not intended to be a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. If you have any concerns about your health or are experiencing symptoms, it is important to consult with a healthcare professional. They will be able to assess your specific situation and provide you with personalised advice and treatment based on your symptoms, body type, allergies (if any), existing medical conditions etc. </span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">It is always a good idea to consult with a healthcare professional before making any decisions about your health.</span></p>', '2022-12-17 12:51:46', 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'anxiety treatment', 'what is anxiety, Anxiety Disorder, how to treat anxiety, mental health awareness, how to control anxiety', 1),
(30, 11, 15, 'Foods to boost metabolism and lose weight', 'Proceed.Fit', 'uploads/Foods_for_efficient_Metabolism.png', 'uploads/1674827281banner_image.png', '<p>Metabolism is a chemical reaction that occurs in our body to generate energy. When we consume food, the metabolism function of the body breaks down the food to generate energy. Energy is required for every function of our body.</p>\r\n<p><iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/qwaKy6YaEFM\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe> <br><a title=\"Subscribe now to get the latest health-related information on our youtube channel.\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/proceedfit\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Subscribe now to get the latest health-related information on our youtube channel.</em></a></p>\r\n<h3>Why metabolism is important?</h3>\r\n<p>Our metabolism continually furnishes our body with energy for fundamental body capabilities like breathing, digestion, repair, and survival. Our body needs basic BMR (basal metabolic rate) to support these capabilities. Various factors that affect the BMR of our body are:<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Age<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Sex<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Muscle mass<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Physical activities<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Type of food you consume</p>\r\n<p>Food is an essential part of our life and a key factor for our survival. We require essential nutrients and, food is the primary source of such nutrients. These nutrients are converted to energy to perform the basic function of life like, &nbsp;breathing, digestion, growth, repairing, and building up the immune system. The process of conversion of energy is known as metabolism.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Some of the essential nutrients for our overall growth are:</h3>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Carbohydrates </strong>- It is essential to keep the body moving and alive. This also builds up body fat.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Dietary fiber</strong> -&nbsp; It supports the absorption of nutrients in the body. It absorbs harmful chemicals and makes feces soft and easy to excrete. It helps prevent obesity</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Fats </strong>- It provides a concentrated source of energy and supports growth.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Proteins</strong> - It builds up the immune system of the body. It is essential for building cells and antibodies.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Water</strong> - It is essential for making the fluid content of the body. It has an important function in creating tears, sweat, and urine. It helps in breaking chemicals in the body.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Iron</strong> - It is a key nutrient for building up hemoglobin. &nbsp;The protein in red blood cells regulates the transport of oxygen to every tissue of the body.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Iodine</strong> - It is very much required for the formation of thyroid hormones. It is required in the development of the brain and nervous system.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Vitamins</strong> - They are very important for making up the immune system of the body and the breakdown of harmful elements.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Folate</strong> - It helps in the prevention of abnormalities in the fetus and helps in generating healthy blood.</p>\r\n<p>The bottom line is, food is the most essential element for metabolism.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>How well our metabolism rate decides how well our body is functioning. Food plays an important role in maintaining the metabolism rate of our body.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>So, what type of food is best for our metabolism?</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Here is the list of food items that are best for boosting the metabolism rate of our body:<br><strong>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Beans</strong><br><strong>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Legumes</strong><br><strong>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Green leafy vegetables</strong><br><strong>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Protein-rich food like meat, fish, nuts, seeds, etc.</strong><br><strong>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tea</strong><br><strong>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Water &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br><strong>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Avocado</strong><br><strong>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Green tea</strong></p>\r\n<p>It is very important to understand the functionality of our metabolism and to know what upsets it.</p>\r\n<p>Not every food is good for metabolism. Various food items may ruin the metabolism function of our body. You are required to cut down on the consumption of these food items or level down the consumption for a better metabolism rate.</p>\r\n<p>Here is the list of various food items you should cut down on, or should avoid consumption of:<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Refined grains </strong>- it spikes the blood sugar level and may create various health-related issues and heart conditions.<br>Refined grains have a high glycemic index and deficiency of fiber which slows down glucose metabolism in the body. Refined grains deteriorate insulin sensitivity.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Alcohol</strong> - Alcohol is considered to be high in calories and it irritates our metabolism process. It is not good for the gastrointestinal tract. It tends to harm our blood sugar level.</p>\r\n<p>Alcohol creates an urge of eating sweets which also affects the functioning of the metabolism process in the body negatively.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;Wheat and refined wheat flour </strong>- They hold a high amount of gluten which slows down the metabolism of our body. Gluten is also known to spike blood sugar levels. It puts an inflammatory burden on the stomach, liver, and immune system of our body which tends to disturb the metabolism regulator of the body.</p>\r\n<p>Refined wheat flour has low nutritional value as compared to whole wheat flour.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Sugar </strong>&ndash; though it treats our taste buds, it does not support our metabolism functioning if consumed in large amounts. It promotes inflammation in the body. It reduces fat metabolism in the body resulting in storing of more fat in the body.</p>\r\n<p>Sweet beverages should also be consumed in limited amount as it slows down metabolism and increases the sugar level. Drinks with a high amount of sugar in them increase the feeling of hunger.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Refined starches </strong>- white rice and white bread lack fiber and nutritional elements. Instead of refined starches, you should opt for whole-grain meals.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Omega-6 fats </strong>- Vegetable oil, chicken, etc contain omega-6 , if not portioned adequately can lead to inflammation. This type of fat if consumed in high quantity disturbs the metabolism of our body. To balance out omega-6 fat you should consume food rich in omega-3 fats.such fats are found in foods like corn, sunflower, mayonnaise, soy, and peanuts.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Dairy </strong>- If you have lactose intolerance and you are consuming dairy then you are giving an open invitation to slow down your metabolism rate. If you have metabolic syndrome then also you are advised to cut down on dairy consumption or to find out substitutes for dairy and include them in the diet.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Junk food </strong>- Junk food though very tasty and pleasing, takes a lot of energy and effort to digest. It slows down the metabolic functioning of the body. Junk food is full of refined starches and refined wheat flour. The added preservative in packed junked food is also very harmful to the body and tends to create inflammation.</p>\r\n<p>What we put into our system decides how well our body will function. So it is very important to look at the nutritional value of the food item before we consume it. After all, what we eat is reflected in our overall personality. It is best to consult a nutritionist or your doctor to know about the best options that fit your body type.</p>\r\n<p>Stay fit, eat healthy and keep your metabolism at its best.<br>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Note : The information provided here is for general informational purposes only and is not intended to be a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. If you have any concerns about your health or are experiencing symptoms, it is important to consult with a healthcare professional. They will be able to assess your specific situation and provide you with personalised advice and treatment based on your symptoms, body type, allergies (if any), existing medical conditions etc. </span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">It is always a good idea to consult with a healthcare professional before making any decisions about your health.</span></p>', '2023-01-27 13:48:01', 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'Metabolism, metabolism booster, increase metabolism,improve metabolism, weight loss, intermittent fasting', 'Metabolism, metabolism booster, increase metabolism,improve metabolism, weight loss, intermittent fasting', 1),
(31, 11, 15, 'How Holozoic Nutrition Affects Your Health ?', 'Proceed.Fit', 'uploads/Holozoic_Nutrition.png', 'uploads/1674828446banner_image.png', '<p>In today\'s fast-growing world where there is ever-increasing awareness about health, everyone is also concerned about nutrition. The nutritional value of food plays an active role in getting a healthy life. To maintain a healthy lifestyle it is crucial to understand what nutrition actually means!</p>\r\n<p>In the biological definition, Holozoic Nutrition means the biochemical and physiological cycle by which an organism utilizes food to help it to survive.</p>\r\n<p>Holozoic nutrition is a type of nutrition in which an organism obtains energy and nutrients by consuming other organisms or organic matter. This is the most common type of nutrition in animals.</p>\r\n<p>In holozoic nutrition, the organism takes in food through its mouth and breaks it down into smaller molecules using digestive enzymes. The smaller molecules are then absorbed into the bloodstream and used for energy or to build new tissues.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Better nutrition leads to various benefits such as:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>&nbsp; &nbsp;Improved infant, child, and maternal health<br>2. &nbsp; &nbsp;Strong Immune system<br>3. &nbsp; &nbsp;Safe pregnancy and childbirth<br>4. &nbsp; &nbsp;Less risk of diseases like diabetes and cardiovascular diseases<br>5. &nbsp; &nbsp;Better learning ability<br>6. &nbsp; &nbsp;Bone strengthening<br>7. &nbsp; &nbsp;Stronger digestive system<br>8. &nbsp; &nbsp;Longevity</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2>Type of nutrition</h2>\r\n<h3>Majorly nutrition are of the following types:</h3>\r\n<p>A. &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Autotrophic nutrition</strong> - The process of preparation of food from simple natural materials like water, carbon dioxide, and mineral salts in the presence of sunlight is called autotrophic nutrition.</p>\r\n<p>The word autotrophic itself explains its meaning i.e. auto-self and trophic-nutrition, which collectively means self-nutrition. Autotrophic organisms use a green-colored pigment called chlorophyll to prepare their food.</p>\r\n<p>B. &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Symbiotic nutrition </strong>- This type of nutrition happens as a result of the mutual association of organisms. Example fungi and lichens.</p>\r\n<p>This mutual association between organisms is for nutrition and shelter.</p>\r\n<p>C. &nbsp; &nbsp;Heterotrophic nutrition- The type of nutrition where organisms depend upon others for food and survival and cannot make their food. All animals, humans, and non-photosynthesizing plants fall under the category of heterotrophic organisms.</p>\r\n<h3>Heterotrophic nutrition is categorized into following types</h3>\r\n<p>1. &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Saprophytic nutrition </strong>- The type of nutrition where organisms feed on dead remains of other organisms for survival is called saprophytic nutrition.</p>\r\n<p>2. &nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;Parasitic nutrition </strong>- Obtaining food from the host that is, other living organisms is parasitic nutrition. The parasites survive by feeding on the blood of the host by living either inside or on the body of the host.</p>\r\n<p>3. &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Holozoic Nutrition </strong>- Engulfing the food into the body through the mouth, digesting it, and absorbing the nutrients and energy from the digested food is known as Holozoic nutrition.</p>\r\n<h2>Let&rsquo;s understand holozoic nutrition in detail</h2>\r\n<p>A type of heterotrophic nutrition described by the assimilation (ingestion) and internal processing of fluids or solid food particles is known as holozoic nutrition. This is a type of nutrition that occurs in the organisms that take food inside their body in the form of solids and liquids.</p>\r\n<p>This type of nutrition is exhibited in protozoa such as amoeba and by humans and most animals where food is taken in solid and liquid form and is further broken down to absorb nutrients.</p>\r\n<h3>Holozoic nutrition is a five-step process:</h3>\r\n<p>1. &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Ingestion </strong>- The process of taking food inside the body through the mouth is called ingestion. This can be done either by swallowing the food. It is also referred to as the initial step of digestion.</p>\r\n<p>Food is taken into the mouth where it is broken down by the teeth into more modest pieces. The presence of food in the mouth sets off a reaction that makes the salivary organs convey watery liquid called saliva to the mouth. Saliva plays the role in making food swallowable and it also helps in breaking down the food.</p>\r\n<p>2. &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Digestion </strong>- The ingested food mixed with saliva is digested with the help of various enzymes. It is the complicated course of transforming the food you eat into nutrients, which the body utilizes for energy, and cell repair for survival and growth. It also creates waste that is to be eliminated from the system.</p>\r\n<p>Digestion is the step that is responsible for the absorption of nutrients into the bloodstream. Digestion in humans occurs in the gastrointestinal tract.</p>\r\n<p>3. &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Absorption</strong> - The energy generated through the digestion of the food is used by the cells of the body. Absorption happens in the body through the following mechanism<br>a) &nbsp; &nbsp;Simple diffusion- Few monosaccharides like glucose, amino acids, etc after digestion diffuse into the blood. It can also be defined as the movement of these monosaccharides from a higher concentration to a lower concentration.</p>\r\n<p>b) &nbsp; &nbsp;Active transport.- Sodium ion electrolytes from the digested foods are actively transported to the blood through this mechanism.</p>\r\n<p>c) &nbsp; &nbsp;Facilitated transport.- In this process carrier proteins helps in the movement of solutes across the membrane.</p>\r\n<p>d) &nbsp; &nbsp;Passive transport.- Simpler food substances after digestion are absorbed into the blood through this process.</p>\r\n<p>4. &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Assimilation</strong>. - In this step, the energy that is being obtained from the digested food is being used by all the cells of the body. It is the process of retention of nutrients, minerals, and different compounds from food as a component of the nourishment of an organism.</p>\r\n<p>The liver plays an important role in the assimilation process. Amino acids obtained from digested foods are used in building up new proteins and fats are used to create energy.</p>\r\n<p>5. &nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;Egestion </strong>- The process of excreting out waste from the body is called egestion. The undigested food is removed from the body through the process of egestion.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Pros and Cons of Holozoic Nutrition</h2>\r\n<h3>The pros of holozoic nutrition</h3>\r\n<p>a) &nbsp; &nbsp;It provides the proper nutrition required by bodies of heterotrophic organisms<br>b) &nbsp; &nbsp;It helps in the proper digestion of food inside the body<br>c) &nbsp; &nbsp;It helps in the generation of energy required by the body<br>d) &nbsp; &nbsp;It strengthens the immune system of the body</p>\r\n<h3>The cons of holozoic nutrition&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>a) &nbsp; &nbsp;Not every secretion from holozoic nutrition is good for small intestines<br>b) &nbsp; &nbsp;Excessive glucose secretion from digested food leads to increase the risk of chronic diseases like diabetes<br>c) &nbsp; &nbsp;Any disturbance in digestion can lead to inflammation in the body</p>\r\n<h2>Best Holozoic foods for humans&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<div class=\"flex-1 overflow-hidden\">\r\n<div class=\"react-scroll-to-bottom--css-jacoa-79elbk h-full dark:bg-gray-800\">\r\n<div class=\"react-scroll-to-bottom--css-jacoa-1n7m0yu\">\r\n<div class=\"flex flex-col items-center text-sm h-full dark:bg-gray-800\">\r\n<div class=\"w-full border-b border-black/10 dark:border-gray-900/50 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 group bg-gray-50 dark:bg-[#444654]\">\r\n<div class=\"text-base gap-6 m-auto md:max-w-2xl lg:max-w-2xl xl:max-w-3xl p-4 md:py-6 flex lg:px-0\">\r\n<div class=\"relative flex w-full flex-col lg:w-[calc(100%-115px)]\">\r\n<div class=\"flex flex-col gap-3\">\r\n<div class=\"min-h-[20px] flex flex-col items-start gap-4 whitespace-pre-wrap\">\r\n<div class=\"markdown prose break-words dark:prose-invert light\">\r\n<p>Different foods provide different nutrients and have different effects on the body. It is important for humans to consume a varied and balanced diet that includes a variety of different types of foods in order to get all the nutrients they need.</p>\r\n<p>That being said, there are certain types of foods that are generally considered to be part of a healthy diet for humans:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Fruits and vegetables</strong>: Rich in vitamins, minerals, and fiber and can help to protect against certain diseases.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Whole grains</strong>: Good source of fiber, vitamins, and minerals and can help to reduce the risk of heart disease and certain types of cancer.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Lean proteins</strong>: These include foods such as beans, nuts, tofu, poultry, and fish. They are important for building and repairing tissues and can help to keep the body feeling full and satisfied.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Healthy fats</strong>: These include foods such as avocados, olive oil, and nuts. These fats can help to protect against heart disease and other chronic conditions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>It is also important to limit the intake of added sugars, saturated and trans fats, and sodium. It\'s a good idea to choose foods that are minimally processed and to aim for a diet that is rich in nutrients and low in calories.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"text-gray-400 flex self-end lg:self-center justify-center mt-2 gap-4 lg:gap-1 lg:absolute lg:top-0 lg:translate-x-full lg:right-0 lg:mt-0 lg:pl-2\">It is very important to have good nutrition to maintain a healthy lifestyle. For proper execution of these five steps of holozoic nutrition, it is important to keep an eye on what we are feeding our mouth and putting into our system. Healthy food means healthy nutrition. Healthy nutrition means better growth, cell repair, and maintenance.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"w-full h-48 flex-shrink-0\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<button class=\"cursor-pointer absolute right-6 bottom-[124px] md:bottom-[120px] z-10 rounded-full border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 text-gray-600 dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-white/10 dark:text-gray-200\"></button></div>\r\n<div class=\"react-scroll-to-bottom--css-jacoa-1n7m0yu\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Note : The information provided here is for general informational purposes only and is not intended to be a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. If you have any concerns about your health or are experiencing symptoms, it is important to consult with a healthcare professional. They will be able to assess your specific situation and provide you with personalised advice and treatment based on your symptoms, body type, allergies (if any), existing medical conditions etc. </span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">It is always a good idea to consult with a healthcare professional before making any decisions about your health.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '2023-01-27 14:07:26', 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'what is holozoic nutrition,holozoic nutrition,holozoic nutrition in amoeba,holozoic mode of nutrition,define holozoic nutrition,what is holozoic nutrition in hindi,holozoic,what is the definition of holozoic nutrition,holozoic nutrition definition,what is the meaning of holozic nutrition,what does holozoic nutrition mean,saprophytic nutrition, what does holozoic nutrition stand for, nutrition, parasitic nutrition, heterotrophic nutrition', 'what is holozoic nutrition,holozoic nutrition,holozoic nutrition in amoeba,holozoic mode of nutrition,define holozoic nutrition,what is holozoic nutrition in hindi,holozoic,what is the definition of holozoic nutrition,holozoic nutrition definition,what is the meaning of holozic nutrition,what does holozoic nutrition mean,saprophytic nutrition,what does holozoic nutrition stand for,nutrition,parasitic nutrition,heterotrophic nutrition', 1),
(32, 11, 16, 'How to Neutralize the bad effects of caffeine?', 'Proceed.Fit', 'uploads/caffiene_yt.png', 'uploads/1674887915banner_image.png', '<p>Caffeine is a natural stimulant commonly found in cocoa plants, tea, and coffee is known as caffeine. When consumed it stimulates the nervous system to increase alertness and attention, energy levels and performance. Coffee is a popular beverage worldwide, and it is consumed in many different forms, including espresso, drip brew, and instant coffee.</p>\r\n<p>These days, 80% of the population worldwide consumes caffeinated items every day and this number increases to 90% for adults in North America.</p>\r\n<h2>How does caffeine work after consumption?</h2>\r\n<p>Once consumed, caffeine is immediately ingested from the stomach into the blood circulatory system. From that point, it goes to the liver and is separated into compounds that can influence the functioning capability of different organs.</p>\r\n<p>The principal impact of caffeine is on the mind. It blocks the effects of adenosine, which is a synapse that makes you feel tired and helps in brain relaxation.</p>\r\n<h2>What are the possible effects of caffeine on the body?</h2>\r\n<p>Let&rsquo;s discuss the effects of caffeine on your body without debating whether it is good or bad.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Caffeine helps you to stay awake by blocking the effects of adenosine.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;It increases blood adrenaline levels<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;It increases the activities of neurotransmitters, norepinephrine, and dopamine.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;It promotes alertness in the body and tends to increase focus.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;It helps in improvising the mood level<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Studies say that 200-300 mg consumption of caffeine every day helps in lowering suicidal thoughts.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Caffeine consumers are also reported to have a lower risk of depression<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;It helps in boosting metabolism<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;It promotes fat burning and enhances exercise performance.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Caffeine is also known to be a psychoactive drug.</strong></p>\r\n<h2>What are the bad effects of caffeine on your body?</h2>\r\n<p>Despite providing many benefits, too much caffeine consumption can have many bad effects on the body.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;It can become an addiction and you can end up forming an addictive habit<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Excess intake of caffeine can cause</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 120px;\">o &nbsp; &nbsp;Anxiety<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Restlessness<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Tremors<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Sleeping troubles<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Irregular heartbeats<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Promotes headaches<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Migraine<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;High blood pressure<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Insomnia<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Dizziness<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Dehydration<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Upset stomach<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Heartburns<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Inflammation<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;ulcers</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Pregnant women are advised to limit the consumption of caffeine as it increases the risk of miscarriages.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;If you are breastfeeding your child then also you should cut down on caffeine consumption as it is passed along with the milk to your baby</p>\r\n<p>If you are addicted to caffeine and consuming it on regular basis, then an immediate stop on its consumption can lead you to experience caffeine withdrawal. Caffeine withdrawals can be recognized by the following symptoms:</p>\r\n<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Headaches<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tiredness<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Drowsiness<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Nausea<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Concentration issues<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Irritability</p>\r\n<p>But don&rsquo;t worry these symptoms don&rsquo;t stay for long, they usually go away after a few days. So if have decided to quit caffeine or limit its consumption go for it.</p>\r\n<h2>How to neutralize the bad effects of caffeine?</h2>\r\n<p>Other than enduring it and keeping yourself away from caffeine, there isn\'t any powerful home solution for clear caffeine from your framework. But you can surely slow down the side effects of caffeine you have already consumed.</p>\r\n<p>Following are the ways you can opt to neutralize the bad effects of caffeine on your body:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Drinking water:</strong> - stay hydrated and drink the proper amount of water to neutralize the effects of caffeine and wash it out of the system. Caffeine dehydrates the body and makes the situation even worst, so drinking water regularly will help you to stay hydrated</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Walk, walk and walk</strong>: - There is no debate on it that walking is very fruitful and has numerous benefits. It helps in boosting brain health and improvising digestion. It is also known to neutralize the effects of too much caffeine consumption.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">It can help in calming down the nervousness that is caused by excessive caffeine consumption. It also helps in soothing that irritation and headache.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Gentle workouts:</strong> - you can also go for some gentle workouts to soothe down the effect of caffeine overdose. Pilates and yoga can be very helpful to cleanse down the bad effects of caffeine.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Breathing exercises:</strong> - practicing breathing exercises can cut down the effect of too much coffee consumption. The deep breathing technique helps to fight anxiety and also helps to relieve stress.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Meditation:</strong> - lying down with closed eyes and doing deep breathing can also help neutralize the side effects of caffeine. Meditation helps in calming down nervous stimulation. It also increases the supply of oxygen to the brain and helps in calming down restlessness.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Eating fiber-rich food:</strong> - Go for a fiber-rich food diet such as beans, lentils, whole grains nuts, and seeds which helps in slowing down the caffeine effects on the bloodstream.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Avoid caffeinated drinks:</strong> - if you are already dealing with the side effects of excessive caffeine then don&rsquo;t feed more of it to your system. Avoid consumption of those drinks and food which are rich in caffeine as it will worsen the situation even more.</p>\r\n<p>Though caffeine can help you to stay active for a long time, however, its overconsumption can lead to hyperactivity and leads to uneasiness.</p>\r\n<p>If you are already addicted to it then also you can make changes in your consumption patterns and lifestyle to put a stop to this addiction and on neutralizing the bad effects that caffeine has made on your body.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Note : The information provided here is for general informational purposes only and is not intended to be a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. If you have any concerns about your health or are experiencing symptoms, it is important to consult with a healthcare professional. They will be able to assess your specific situation and provide you with personalised advice and treatment based on your symptoms, body type, allergies (if any), existing medical conditions etc.&nbsp;It is always a good idea to consult with a healthcare professional before making any decisions about your health.</span></p>', '2023-01-28 06:38:35', 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'caffeine,caffeine side effects,bad effects of caffeine,caffeine addiction,health effects of caffeine,benefits of caffeine,side effects of caffeine,is caffeine bad,toxic effects of caffeine,coffee side effects,quit caffeine,quitting caffeine,caffeine brain effects,caffeine effects on sleep,quitting caffeine effects,coffee health effects,dr. berg on caffeine effects,caffeine benefits,harmful effects of coffee,get rid of caffeine jitters', 'caffeine,caffeine side effects,bad effects of caffeine,caffeine addiction,health effects of caffeine,benefits of caffeine,side effects of caffeine,is caffeine bad,toxic effects of caffeine,coffee side effects,quit caffeine,quitting caffeine,caffeine brain effects,caffeine effects on sleep,quitting caffeine effects,coffee health effects,dr. berg on caffeine effects,caffeine benefits,harmful effects of coffee,get rid of caffeine jitters', 1);
