(33, 10, 17, 'Avoid Tooth Cavity - Life long', 'Proceed.Fit', 'uploads/avoid_tooth_cavity.png', 'uploads/1674888251banner_image.png', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Teeth are a very important part of our body. It not only supports your eating mechanism but it is also important every time we smile, talk, frown and make facial expressions. Teeth play an essential role to begin the process of digestion.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Your teeth alignment inside your mouth gives shape to your face. Each type of tooth is unique and important in its own way and each one has a specific function to perform.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Importance of teeth</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As already mentioned above teeth are an important element of your mouth. Healthy teeth help us to:-</p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">chew and digest our food better.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Helps us in talking and speaking clearly</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Gives us the confidence to smile without being conscious.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Keeps your mouth odourless.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Prevents you from experiencing that tooth pain.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">They influence your social and personal lives.<br><br></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A healthy smile can win thousands of hearts and to keep your smile healthy you need to keep your teeth healthy. To keep your teeth healthy you need to maintain the proper oral hygiene.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">The proper Oral hygiene.</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Oral hygiene is very important to keep your teeth healthy and strong. By brushing our teeth twice daily, maintaining a low-in-sugar diet and regularly visits to our dental professional we can maintain our oral hygiene.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Whatever you consume goes to your stomach and propagates into the entire body. So it\'s important to have oral hygiene day long.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A proper oral hygiene helps to reduce the risk of various dental issues like</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 40px;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tooth cavity<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Dental decay<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Gum diseases<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tooth loss<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Oral infections<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Bacterial accumulation<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Plaque build-up<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Smelly breathe</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A visit to a dentist every six months for a routine oral check-up also helps in maintaining oral hygiene and can also help in avoiding tooth cavities.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What is tooth cavity?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tiny holes in the tooth due to a permanent damage and decaying of tooth is called tooth cavity. Cavities and tooth rot are among the world\'s normal dental issues. They\'re particularly normal in kids, teenagers and old peoples. But this doesn&rsquo;t means those in their twenties, thirties or forties cannot get cavities. If you have teeth you have a risk of getting tooth cavity.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Moreover, if you got a cavity and you are not treating it, you are making things even more worst. They can prompt serious toothache, tooth contamination and tooth loss.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What are the symptoms that show you are dealing with tooth cavity?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Depending upon the extent and location of your tooth symptoms of the cavity can vary. At the beginning of the occurrence of the cavity, there might be no symptoms at all but as the decay gets longer and worsen it starts showing symptoms like:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 40px;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Sudden pain without any cause, and toothache.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Sensitivity in the tooth.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Mild sharp pain while eating or drinking hot and cold food items.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Holes in tooth.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tooth decay.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Pain on biting anything.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Black stains on the tooth surface.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Bad breath.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tenderness on eating sweet dishes.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Unpleasant taste in the mouth.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sometimes you don&rsquo;t even come to know that your tooth has a cavity until it get worst. So it is very important to visit your dentist on regular intervals and getting your dental checkup done. Your mouth also feels healthy and fresh if you get your cleaning done time to time.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Follow one rule to maintain healthy teeth, visit your dentist whenever you feel pain in your tooth.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What are the causes behind tooth cavity?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tooth decay is the main reason of tooth cavity. Tooth decay is the process that occurs overtime. There are the following reasons for tooth decay:-</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br>1. &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Plaque forms-</strong> It is a kind of clear sticky layer that covers your teeth. This happens because of eating too much of sugary items and starchy food and not cleaning the teeth well. If you don&rsquo;t clean your teeth well after eating sweet and sugary items, bacteria quickly start feeding on it and forms plaque.<br>Plaque on staying for long on your teeth starts to form tartar which makes it more difficult to clean the plaque off your teeth.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2. &nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;Swollen gums and roots</strong>- As tooth rot creates bacteria and acid continues to destroy your teeth moving close to the internal tooth material (pulp). The pulp contains nerves and blood vessels. This leads to swollen pulp and gums. The tooth keeps on rotting and the pain can reach till the bone</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3. &nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;Holes in the enamel-</strong> When the plaque accumulates on your teeth, its acid remove minerals from enamel. This leads to erosion and holes in enamels. This enamel holes are also known to be the initial stage of cavity.&nbsp;<br>If left untreated bacteria through these holes can reach the next layer of your tooth called dentin. Dentin is less resistant to acid and rots very fast. Dentin being in direct contact to nerve starts causing sensitivity.</p>\r\n<h2>How to avoid Tooth cavities?</h2>\r\n<p>As mentioned above also it is very important to maintain healthy teeth and to avoid tooth cavity.</p>\r\n<p>There are following ways you can opt for to avoid tooth cavity:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Brush with toothpaste containing fluoride- make a habit of brushing twice a day especially after your last meal. Use fluoride enriched toothpaste for cleaning the residue of your food from your teeth.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Regular visits to dentist- Visit to your dentist at regular intervals helps in keeping teeth healthy. It also helps in early spotting of the problem in your teeth.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Sealants- A sealant is a defensive plastic covering applied to the biting surface of back teeth. It helps in protecting enamel from plaque attack.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Avoid sugary items- Too much consumption of sweet and sugary foods leads to creation of plaque. It accelerates the bacteria attack and acid creation that destroys enamel.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Flossing- using floss to clean your teeth can help you getting rid of that stuck food particles between your teeth and preventing bacteria formation.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Apart from these few eating habits can also help in avoiding tooth cavity. Few changes you can make in your eating habits are:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 40px;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Limit fruit juice consumption<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Limit your cookies, chocolates and candies consumption<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Limit sweet beverages<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Limit your snacking over junk food<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Avoid substances that dry your mouth.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Avoid sticky food<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Avoid hard to crack food<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Stop consuming extremely hot or extremely cold food.<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Limit your wine consumption<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Limit coffee and tea consumption</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Remember a healthy tooth means healthy mouth and a healthy mouth means a beautiful smile. So keep your teeth healthy and your smile wide.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-01-28 06:44:11', 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'tooth cavity,tooth decay,tooth,cavity,dental cavity,tooth filling,heal tooth decay,front tooth cavity,tooth cavity filling,tooth filling cavity,prevent tooth decay,tooth pain,tooth cavity pain,tooth with cavity,stop tooth cavity,tooth cavity filler,tooth cavites,what does a cavity look like on a tooth,tooth cavities,how to stop tooth cavity,cure tooth decay,tooth cavity home remedy,reverse tooth decay,tooth cavity pain relief home remedy', 'tooth cavity,tooth decay,tooth,cavity,dental cavity,tooth filling,heal tooth decay,front tooth cavity,tooth cavity filling,tooth filling cavity,prevent tooth decay,tooth pain,tooth cavity pain,tooth with cavity,stop tooth cavity,tooth cavity filler,tooth cavites,what does a cavity look like on a tooth,tooth cavities,how to stop tooth cavity,cure tooth decay,tooth cavity home remedy,reverse tooth decay,tooth cavity pain relief home remedy', 1),
(34, 11, 18, 'Foods to Unclog Arteries', 'Proceed.Fit', 'uploads/unclog_arteries.png', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Healthy and unclogged arteries are very important for the normal functioning of the heart and thereby whole body. It is one of the main components regulating blood circulation in the body. It is the major part of the blood circulatory system. It is a tube-like structure that transports fluids like blood &amp; lymph to and fro every part of the body.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Arteries are majorly responsible for the transportation of oxygen, hormones, and nutrients in our bodies.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Arteries are made out of smooth muscle permitting dilation and contraction through the parasympathetic nervous system.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Because the artery is responsible for carrying oxygenated blood from the heart to other parts of the body they need to have a clear and unclogged passage. Clear and unclogged passage helps in the proper flow of blood to and fro.</p>\r\n<h2>What are the reasons for clogged arteries?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Too much cholesterol is a reason for many health complications. It is very important to manage cholesterol levels for a healthy and stress-free life. It is one of the major reasons responsible for clogged arteries.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Cholesterol gets accumulated on the walls of the arteries making the passage narrow and blocked. This blockage reduces the flow of blood through arteries and not every part of the body including the heart gets the proper amount of oxygenated blood.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Inflammation is also responsible for clogged arteries. This clogged artery situation is also known as Coronary artery disease or arterial plaque.</p>\r\n<h2>What happens if you have clogged arteries?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When your artery is clogged and the passage for blood to travel is narrow your heart is unable to get enough oxygenated blood. This can lead to Angina (a situation of pain in the chest because of reduced blood flow to the heart) and uneasiness in breathing.</p>\r\n<p>If there is complete clogging in the arteries, it can lead to a heart attack.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Signs and symptoms of clogged arteries.</h3>\r\n<p>Clogged arteries show the following symptoms in the body:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Crushing pain in the chest</li>\r\n<li>Pressure on chest</li>\r\n<li>Pain in arms and shoulders</li>\r\n<li>Shortness of breath</li>\r\n<li>Abnormal sweating</li>\r\n<li>Heart palpitations</li>\r\n<li>Neck pain</li>\r\n<li>Jaw pain</li>\r\n<li>Nausea</li>\r\n<li>Fatigue</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Can you unclog your clogged arteries?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you have gone through tests and it shows that you are dealing with clogged arteries, don&rsquo;t panic. Panic will worsen the situation even more. Visit your doctor and ask for his guidance to help you out. You can also make efforts to improve your situation. You can opt for a lifestyle that will help you in clearing down the clogs and remove the blockage from arteries. Some of such lifestyle changes that you can make are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Exercising and physical activities</li>\r\n<li>Stress management</li>\r\n<li>Dietary changes</li>\r\n<li>Management of sleeping cycles</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How food helps in unclogging arteries?</h2>\r\n<p>Involving some foods in your diet can help in clearing up the blocked arteries. Some of the foods that might help are:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Broccoli</strong>- This cruciferous vegetable rich in Vitamin K is very beneficial to deal with unclogged arteries.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Broccoli helps in preventing calcification in arteries and also helps in stress management. It is a very good vegetable to control blood pressure too. So include Broccoli in your diet and see the magic of this wonderful vegetable.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Garlic&nbsp;</strong>- It is known to control blood pressure and to reduce the amount of plaque in the arteries, thus supporting the clearing of blocked arteries. It also helps in preventing arteries from becoming stiff because of plaque accumulation.</p>\r\n<p>A compound called allicin is released from garlic which reduces the risk of heart-related complications. It also slows down the oxidation of LDL.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Spices&nbsp;</strong>- &nbsp;Spices like pepper, chili, ginger, and cinnamon help in preventing artery clogging. They help in improving blood cholesterol levels thus preventing the accumulation of lipids in arteries.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Spice like cinnamon has anti-inflammatory properties and prevents platelets from clumping in the blood.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Pomegranate&nbsp;</strong>- Rich in antioxidants, pomegranate has several heart-protecting benefits. It helps in slowing down the cholesterol build-up in the blood and also in reducing the LDL (low-density lipoprotein).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Pomegranate protects the walls of arteries from getting damaged. Production of nitric acid is accelerated in the body on the consumption of pomegranate juice which helps in improving blood flow and reducing the risk of clots formation in the blood.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Turmeric</strong>- Rich in curcumin, turmeric has anti-inflammatory properties. It helps in reducing fatty deposits in arteries and also reduces arterial inflammation. Include turmeric in your diet the way you like and see its magic. It also improves the endothelial function in the body.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Asparagus&nbsp;</strong>- It is a very fibrous vegetable rich in vitamins like B1, B2, C, E, and K. It is also known as natural artery-clearing food. It prevents the formation of blood clots in the arteries and also helps in lowering down and controlling blood pressure.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is an amazing vegetable to keep you away from the risk of many cardiovascular diseases. If you are already dealing with clogged arteries, introduce this green vegetable to your diet and it will help in clearing the blockage and unclogging the arteries.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Berries&nbsp;</strong>- Berries like blackberries, cranberries, raspberries, and blueberries are very good sources of natural fiber, vitamins, and minerals. They have anti-inflammatory properties and are known to improve the health of your heart.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Berries reduce the risk of the rising level of LDL and blood sugar levels. They help in unclogging the arteries because of their anti-inflammatory property. They also prevent artery damage and increase HDL.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Tomatoes&nbsp;</strong>- Eating raw tomatoes as a salad can be an amazing vegetable to unclog your clogged arteries. Tomatoes contain lycopene, which is known to be your heart&rsquo;s best friend. It is also helpful in reducing the cholesterol level in the blood.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Beans&nbsp;</strong>- It is an excellent way to keep an eye on your cholesterol level. Include beans in your diet and maintain your cholesterol levels also protect yourself from the risk of clogged arteries.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It helps in reducing blood pressure levels and lowering LDL, thus helping in clearing the clogs too.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is very important to remember that a healthy diet is just one component of maintaining healthy arteries. Other lifestyle factors, such as not smoking, getting regular physical activity, and managing stress, can also play a role in preventing or managing plaque buildup in the arteries. If you have concerns about your risk of heart disease or your overall cardiovascular health, it is important to talk to your healthcare provider.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', '2022-12-23 15:15:19', 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'foods that unclog arteries,unclog arteries,foods to unclog arteries,foods that unclog arteries naturally,clogged arteries,foods to clean arteries,clean your arteries,unclog arteries naturally,clean arteries,how to unclog arteries,best foods to unclog arteries,foods that naturally unclog arteries,blocked arteries,unclog arteries fast,how to clean arteries naturally,how to clean arteries,cure blocked arteries,foods that clear arteries', 'foods that unclog arteries,unclog arteries,foods to unclog arteries,foods that unclog arteries naturally,clogged arteries,foods to clean arteries,clean your arteries,unclog arteries naturally,clean arteries,how to unclog arteries,best foods to unclog arteries,foods that naturally unclog arteries,blocked arteries,unclog arteries fast,how to clean arteries naturally,how to clean arteries,cure blocked arteries,foods that clear arteries', 1),
(35, 12, 19, 'Ways to improve your fitness and health', 'Proceed.Fit', 'uploads/Ways_to_improve_your_fitness_and_health.png', 'uploads/1674722324banner_image.jpg', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Once said by the Dalai Lama, &ldquo;Great health can&rsquo;t be bought on the market, but it&rsquo;s extremely valuable.&rdquo; As we struggle to fulfil our responsibilities in everyone&rsquo;s life, we frequently forget to take care of ourselves. The stress levels continue to rise until, one day, a major collapse of our health may awaken us to the fact that we have forgotten to care for one important thing&mdash;our health.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">People&rsquo;s susceptibility to diseases such as obesity, diabetes, heart attacks, and hypertension has increased as a result of an unhealthy lifestyle. This has resulted in grave consequences for the near future. As a result, it is critical that we prioritise our health alongside our work. Moderation in our eating habits, daily exercise, and a balanced work life can all make a significant difference in our health and body. When a person maintains his or her mental and physical fitness, his or her actions and decisions become more practical, logical, and efficient, and he or she is more successful in life. Furthermore, our personality is influenced by our physical health.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A physically or mentally Ill person faces numerous challenges in life, even if they rely on others for their basic needs. So it is beneficial to maintain good health, both physically and mentally, without the assistance of others. Wealth and health are correlated to each other. We need money to maintain good health, and we need good health to earn money. But it is also true that we can live without money, but we cannot live with unhealthy habits. A healthy state of mind and body helps us all the time and encourages us to do something better in our lives rather than just earn money.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are many ways a person can improve his or her health without any assistance. These tips are issued by the World Health Organization (WHO) itself and are pretty reliable for achieving stable health.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">These tips are for everyone, regardless of age, and must be followed by everyone to&nbsp;improve their fitness and health.</h3>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Have a balanced diet</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In India, it is believed that what we eat is what we become. Eating healthy can cure chronic diseases like heart disease, tumours, strokes, and diabetes. It may also help you maintain a <a href=\"../blog_details.php?blog=30&amp;title=Foods-to-boost-metabolism-and-lose-weight\">healthy weight</a> and reduce your risk of developing certain cancers. A balanced diet includes the proper amount of calories, proteins, vitamins, and minerals. A well-balanced diet should also include bioactive products such as dietary fibre, antioxidants, and nutraceuticals, all of which have health benefits. The most crucial rule of healthy eating is that no meal should be skipped. Meal skipping lowers your metabolic rate. Normal eating consists of three main meals and two snacks in between. In addition, never skip breakfast. It is the most important meal of the day.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Exercise daily</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Exercising on a regular basis is important for maintaining a healthy state. Physical activity can improve your brain health, help you manage your weight, lower your risk of disease, strengthen your bones and muscles, and improve your ability to do everyday tasks. Adults who sit less and engage in moderate-to-vigorous physical activity reap health benefits. Regular exercise strengthens the cardiovascular system to deliver more oxygen to the body with each heartbeat and the pulmonary system to increase the efficiency of oxygen delivery to the body.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Prioritize your mental health</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Decrease stress in your daily life. Stress reduces mental activity and affects the normal metabolism of the body. Mental health is more important than ever. It affects every aspect of our lifestyles. Everything we do, think, or say is influenced by our mental health, which in turn influences our physique. Maintaining a healthy mental state and treating any mental health conditions are critical for restoring constructive behaviours, emotions, and thoughts. Focusing on mental health care can boost productivity, improve our self-image, and strengthen relationships.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Give up bad habits</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Smoking, tobacco, alcohol, and drugs are all harmful to your health. Smoking can harm the lungs because the smoker inhales nicotine as well as other chemicals. Cigarettes have been linked to an increased risk of developing lung cancer. Men are more at risk than women. Alcohol is the leading cause of liver diseases like cirrhosis and liver dysfunction. Dehydration-related effects, like nausea, headaches, and dizziness, come along with the side effects of alcohol. Drugs, on the other hand, directly attack mental health. Drugging can cause amnesia (loss of memory), alopecia (loss of hair), gastrointestinal issues, sedation, euphoria, bradycardia, bronchoconstriction, urinary retention, and the list goes on and on.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Overdoing anything is injurious to health</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Overeating, oversleeping, overthinking, and overdoing everything harm the health. Do things in moderation to get the best results for your health.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Improve sleep-wake cycles</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Good sleep is an extremely important aspect of our daily lives. Sleep has been extensively influences our quality of life in a variety of ways, including our behaviour, work efficiency, immunity, and mental health maintenance.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Lessen the use of sugar and salt in food</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sugar consumption increases the risk of tooth decay and overweight. Consuming more sugar can cause diabetes mellitus type 2. Sugar-free products are the best replacements for sugar. Salty foods can cause hypertension and heart problems with long-term usage.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Strengthen your immune system</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The immune system is the protector of our body. Each and every disease first affects the immune system before attacking any other system. Hence, developing and strengthening our first line of defence becomes crucial to surviving. Vaccinations, immunity supplements, and vitamins like vitamin C.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In conclusion, health is wealth, and without that wealth, no other wealth is worthy. Staying healthy is essential for living a happy life free of diseases. Furthermore, at this time, a large proportion of people are obese, which means they are overweight and unhealthy. A daily routine of fitness exercise and a healthy diet can increase your lifetime, and you can feel better just by applying these simple steps to your life.<br>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-01-28 06:33:48', 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'how to improve your health,how to improve your health and wellness,health,fitness,how to improve your overall health,how to improve your health and fitness,improve your health and fitness,improve your health and fitness routine,how to improve your overall health and wellness,how to improve your health and wellbeing,health and wellness,how to improve your heart health,how to improve your fitness,where to begin your health and fitness journey', 'how to improve your health,how to improve your health and wellness,health,fitness,how to improve your overall health,how to improve your health and fitness,improve your health and fitness,improve your health and fitness routine,how to improve your overall health and wellness,how to improve your health and wellbeing,health and wellness,how to improve your heart health,how to improve your fitness,where to begin your health and fitness journey', 1),
(36, 10, 17, 'How to avoid tooth cavity ?', 'Proceed.Fit', 'uploads/How_to_avoid_tooth_cavity_.png', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Teeth are a very important part of our body. It not only supports your eating mechanism but it is also important every time we smile, talk, frown and make facial expressions. Teeth play an essential role to begin the process of digestion.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Your teeth alignment inside your mouth gives shape to your face. Each type of tooth is unique and important in its own way and each one has a specific function to perform.</p>\r\n<p><iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/vCl5rnBn92E\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Importance of teeth</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As already mentioned above teeth are an important element of your mouth. Healthy teeth help us to:-</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px; text-align: justify;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;chew and digest our food better<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;helps us in talking and speaking clearly<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;gives us the confidence to smile without being conscious<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;keeps your mouth odourless<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;It influences your social and personal lives<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;They help you to present yourself with confidence</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A healthy smile can win thousands of hearts and to keep your smile healthy you need to keep your teeth healthy. To keep your teeth healthy you need to maintain proper oral hygiene.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">The proper Oral hygiene</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Oral hygiene is very important to keep your teeth healthy and strong. By brushing our teeth twice daily, maintaining a low-in-sugar diet and regularly visits to our dental professional we can maintain our oral hygiene.<br>Proper oral hygiene helps to reduce the risk of various dental issues like</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px; text-align: justify;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tooth cavity<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Dental decay<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Gum diseases<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tooth loss<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Oral infections<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Bacterial accumulation<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Plaque build-up<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Smelly breathe</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What is tooth cavity?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tiny holes in the tooth due to permanent damage and decaying of the tooth is called tooth cavity. Cavities and tooth rot are among the world\'s normal dental issues. They\'re particularly normal in kids, teenagers and old people. But this doesn&rsquo;t mean those in their twenties, thirties or forties cannot get cavities. If you have teeth you have a risk of getting tooth cavities.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Moreover, if you got a cavity and you are not treating it, you are making things even more worst. They can prompt serious toothache, tooth contamination and tooth loss.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What are the symptoms that show you are dealing with tooth cavities?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Depending upon the extent and location of your tooth symptoms of the cavity can vary. At the beginning of the occurrence of cavity, there might be no symptoms at all but as the decay gets longer and worsen it starts showing symptoms like:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px; text-align: justify;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Sudden pain without any cause, and toothache<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Sensitivity in the tooth<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Mild sharp pain while eating or drinking hot and cold food items<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Holes in tooth<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tooth decay<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Pain on biting anything<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Black stains on the tooth surface<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Bad breathe<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tenderness on eating sweet dishes<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Unpleasant taste in the mouth</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sometimes you don&rsquo;t even come to know that your tooth has a cavity until it get worst. So it is very important to visit your dentist on regular intervals and get your dental checkup done. Your mouth also feels healthy and fresh if you get your cleaning done from time to time.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What are the causes behind tooth cavities?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tooth decay is the main reason of tooth cavities. Tooth decay is a process that occurs over time. There are the following reasons for tooth decay:-</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">1.&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Plaque forms</strong> - It is a kind of clear sticky layer that covers your teeth. This happens because of eating too much of sugary items and starchy food and not cleaning the teeth well. If you don&rsquo;t clean your teeth well after eating sweet and sugary items, bacteria quickly start feeding on it and forms plaque.<br>Plaque on staying for long on your teeth starts to form tartar which makes it more difficult to clean the plaque off your teeth.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp; <strong>Swollen gums and roots</strong> - As tooth rot creates bacteria and acid continues to destroy your teeth moving close to the internal tooth material (pulp). The pulp contains nerves and blood vessels. This leads to swollen pulp and gums.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;<strong> Holes in the enamel </strong>- When the plaque accumulates on your teeth, its acid removes minerals from the enamel. This leads to erosion and holes in enamels. These enamel holes are also known to be the initial stage of the cavity.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If left untreated bacteria through these holes can reach the next layer of your tooth called dentin. Dentin is less resistant to acid and rots very fast. Dentin being in direct contact to nerve starts causing sensitivity.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">How to avoid Tooth cavity?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are the following ways you can opt for to avoid tooth cavities:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">1. &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Brush with toothpaste containing fluoride</strong>: &nbsp;make a habit of brushing twice a day, especially after your last meal. Use fluoride-enriched toothpaste for cleaning the residue of your food from your teeth.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2. &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Regular visits to dentist</strong>: Visit to your dentist at regular intervals helps in keeping teeth healthy. It also helps in early spotting of the problem in your teeth.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3. &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Sealants</strong>: A sealant is a defensive plastic covering applied to the biting surface of back teeth. It helps in protecting enamel from plaque attack.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4. &nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;Avoid sugary items</strong>: &nbsp;Too much consumption of sweet and sugary foods leads to the creation of plaque. It accelerates the bacteria attack and acid creation that destroys enamel.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">5. &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Flossing</strong>: &nbsp;using floss to clean your teeth can help you get rid of that stuck food particles between your teeth and prevent bacteria formation.<br><br></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;A few changes you can make in your eating habits are:</h3>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px; text-align: justify;\">1. &nbsp; &nbsp;Limit fruit juice consumption<br>2. &nbsp; &nbsp;Limit your cookies, chocolates and candies consumption<br>3. &nbsp; &nbsp;Limit sweet beverages<br>4. &nbsp; &nbsp;Limit your snacking over junk food<br>5. &nbsp; &nbsp;Avoid substances that dry your mouth.<br>6. &nbsp; &nbsp;Avoid sticky food<br>7. &nbsp; &nbsp;Avoid hard to crack food<br>8. &nbsp; &nbsp;Stop consuming extremely hot or extremely cold food.<br>9. &nbsp; &nbsp;Limit your wine consumption<br>10. &nbsp; &nbsp;Limit coffee and tea consumption</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Summary</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;Tooth cavities are a common dental issue that can occur due to erosion of the enamel of the teeth. Cavities can cause pain, infection, and tooth loss if left untreated. Good oral hygiene, includes brushing and flossing regularly, can help prevent cavities. It is also important to visit a dentist regularly for cleanings and checkup. If you do have a cavity, your dentist can recommend treatment options such as fillings, crowns, or root canals. By taking care of your teeth, you can maintain healthy teeth and a beautiful smile.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Note : The information provided here is for general informational purposes only and is not intended to be a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. If you have any concerns about your health or are experiencing symptoms, it is important to consult with a healthcare professional. They will be able to assess your specific situation and provide you with personalised advice and treatment based on your symptoms, body type, allergies (if any), existing medical conditions etc. It is always a good idea to consult with a healthcare professional before making any decisions about your health.</p>', '2023-01-06 12:53:25', 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'cavity,tooth cavity,tooth decay,tooth,how to stop tooth decay,how to prevent tooth decay,teeth cavity,how to prevent cavities,prevent tooth decay,how to avoid cavity in teeth,tooth cavities,tooth cavity home remedy,dental cavity,teeth,tooth decay treatment,stop tooth cavity,reverse tooth decay,tooth cavity pain,tooth with cavity,how to prevent cavity in teeth,front tooth cavity,stop tooth decay,how to,tooth cavity filler,how to avoid', 'cavity,tooth cavity,tooth decay,tooth,how to stop tooth decay,how to prevent tooth decay,teeth cavity,how to prevent cavities,prevent tooth decay,how to avoid cavity in teeth,tooth cavities,tooth cavity home remedy,dental cavity,teeth,tooth decay treatment,stop tooth cavity,reverse tooth decay,tooth cavity pain,tooth with cavity,how to prevent cavity in teeth,front tooth cavity,stop tooth decay,how to,tooth cavity filler,how to avoid', 1),
(37, 10, 17, 'what is xanthomas?', 'Proceed.Fit', 'uploads/Xanthomas.png', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Xanthomas is a &nbsp;skin condition in which certain fats develop underneath the skin. It looks like the small blemished bumps on the skin are due to fat buildup under the skin. These bumps on the skin are not dangerous in themselves but they are in many cases a side effect of another medical issue like diabetes or high cholesterol.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What are the possible causes of Xanthomas?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Xanthomas are normal, among old people and those with high blood lipids that is fat.<br>You likely need testing to figure out the causes of the same. A few circumstances that lead to xanthomas can be dangerous and life-threatening if not treated. High cholesterol and triglycerides are a kind of blood lipid that can become the cause of Xanthomas.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If a person is dealing with any other severe health problem which may result in increased blood lipid levels can also be the reason for xanthomas.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Some of the health conditions that can become the reason for xanthomas eruption in the skin are:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px; text-align: justify;\">1. &nbsp; &nbsp;High cholesterol<br>2. &nbsp; &nbsp;Diabetes<br>3. &nbsp; &nbsp;familial hypercholesterolemia<br>4. &nbsp; &nbsp;Metabolic disorders<br>5. &nbsp; &nbsp;Liver cirrhosis<br>6. &nbsp; &nbsp;Active thyroid<br>7. &nbsp; &nbsp;Cancers<br>8. &nbsp; &nbsp;Pancreatitis (swelling in the pancreas)</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">How it looks like and where on the body then tends to appear?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Xanthomas eruptions on the skin may vary from size to size. Some may be very small and some may be bigger than 3 inches in diameter. They may erupt on any part of the body even internally. The most common regions of the body can occur in our knees, hands, elbows, joints, buttocks, and feet.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">They may also appear on the eyelids without any underlying medical condition. The type of xanthomas that appears on the eyelid is called Xanthelasma palpebra.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What are tests to go through?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you notice this kind of eruption on any part of your body then go and see your doctor. Your doctor might suggest you go through various tests to make sure the main cause for it and to check that it is not cancerous.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You are also suggested to get your lipid profile done to know the cholesterol level in the blood.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The doctor might also suggest a few tests like; diabetes, liver test, thyroid test, etc.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">How to treat them?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The doctor may use laser treatment and surgery to remove the xanthomas from your skin but there is a possibility that they might return after removal.<br>You are required to keep a check on your lipid levels and food intake first if you want to get rid of these bumps.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Can you get rid of xanthomas on your own?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can make lifestyle changes and a few changes in your diet which can help in getting rid of these bumps naturally.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Firstly, you are required to understand the main reason for it, which is the high level of cholesterol in the blood. You need to control it first.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you believe in Ayurvedic science you can opt for some remedies Ayurvedic science suggests curing Xanthomas naturally.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Some of them are:</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Castor oil&nbsp; </strong>- Ricinoleic acid of castor oil is very beneficial for the skin. Applying castor oil on the bumps can help in reducing their size by breaking down the unwanted deposit of fat over that area. Apply the castor oil on the bump using a cotton ball.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Garlic&nbsp;</strong>- Garlic works as a magical remedy for xanthomas. It is a very good source to control the cholesterol level in the blood. Upper lip bumps can be cured very fast using garlic.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You are required to crush down some cloves of garlic and make it into a paste. You have to apply the paste on the bumps. If in case it causes a burning sensation on the applied area you can also mix some castor oil with the paste and then apply it. Apply the paste and leave it for a maximum of 20 minutes on every application.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Fenugreek seeds&nbsp;</strong>- These seeds are blessed with amazing properties and help in reducing fatty deposits. It helps in breaking down lipid accumulation.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Onions&nbsp;</strong>- rich in sulphur onion helps in lowering the bad cholesterol level in the blood. Being acidic, it helps in breaking down the fat deposit and flattening the bumps.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Banana peels&nbsp;</strong>- Fresh banana peels rich in antioxidants helps in breaking down these fat deposits and reducing the size of xanthomas naturally.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can also make some changes in your diet to deal with these fat deposits.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px; text-align: justify;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Add citrus fruits to your diet<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Cut down on oily and fried food<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Quit tobacco<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Cut down on sugary items to control diabetes</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are several types of xanthoma, including xanthelasma, tuberous xanthoma, and eruptive xanthoma. The treatment of xanthoma depends on the type and location of the lesions, as well as the underlying cause. Treatment options may include dietary changes (as explained above), medications, or surgical removal of the lesions.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is important to take medical advice if you notice any unusual bumps or changes in the appearance of your skin. Early diagnosis and treatment can help prevent the progression of xanthoma.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Note : The information provided here is for general informational purposes only and is not intended to be a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. If you have any concerns about your health or are experiencing symptoms, it is important to consult with a healthcare professional. They will be able to assess your specific situation and provide you with personalised advice and treatment based on your symptoms, body type, allergies (if any), existing medical conditions etc. It is always a good idea to consult with a healthcare professional before making any decisions about your health.</p>', '2023-01-11 09:40:04', 1, 1, 1, 0, 1, 'xanthoma,xanthomas,xanthoma removal,xanthoma eye,xanthoma meaning,xanthoma treatment,xanthoma definition,xanthoma vs xanthelasma,xanthomata,xanthoma pronounce,xanthoma removal cream,skin xanthoma,xanthoma home,xanthoma causes,xanthoma on skin,xanthoma dr berg,eyelid xanthoma,what is xanthoma,xanthoma remedies,penyakit xanthoma,penyebab xanthoma,xanthomas remedy,remedy for xanthoma,dr. berg on xanthoma,xanthoma explained,xanthoma histology', 'xanthoma,xanthomas,xanthoma removal,xanthoma eye,xanthoma meaning,xanthoma treatment,xanthoma definition,xanthoma vs xanthelasma,xanthomata,xanthoma pronounce,xanthoma removal cream,skin xanthoma,xanthoma home,xanthoma causes,xanthoma on skin,xanthoma dr berg,eyelid xanthoma,what is xanthoma,xanthoma remedies,penyakit xanthoma,penyebab xanthoma,xanthomas remedy,remedy for xanthoma,dr. berg on xanthoma,xanthoma explained,xanthoma histology', 1);
