(43, 12, 19, '10 SUCCESSFUL WEIGHT LOSS Tips', 'Proceed.Fit', 'uploads/1674934312banner_image1.png', 'uploads/1674934312banner_image.png', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Numerous health issues might result from being overweight or obese such as diabetes, heart disease, and high blood pressure. Adopting a balanced lifestyle and consuming nutritious food are essential for managing weight and maintaining overall health. Simple and achievable actions, such as regular exercise, portion control, and making healthy food choices, can help individuals lose weight and maintain a healthy weight in the long term.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Following are 10 SUCCESSFUL WEIGHT LOSS Tips</h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">1) Eat nutritionally dense foods.</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Reduce your intake of saturated fats, which are strongly associated with the occurrence of coronary heart disease, and eliminate trans fats from your diet.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Prefer foods that are loaded with nutrients such as Fresh produce, fish, legumes, Nuts, Seeds, Whole grains like oatmeal and brown rice.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Foods to stay away from include:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">- Foods with extra butter, sugar, and oils<br>- Processed or red meat that is fatty<br>- Bakery items<br>- Wheat bread</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br>2) Keep a food and weight diary.</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Self-monitoring is essential for achieving weight loss success. To keep track of all the food they eat each day, people can use a paper diary, a smartphone app, or a special website. By keeping a weekly weight log, you will track your development.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">3) Eliminate liquid calories.</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you drink soda, tea, juice, or alcohol that has been sweetened with sugar, you might easily ingest hundreds of calories each day. These are referred to as empty calories since they offer additional energy content but no nutritional advantages.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">4) Measure servings and control portions.</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">At times, low-calorie foods can also cause weight gain when consumed in excess portions. As a result, it\'s best to refrain from calculating portion sizes and from eating food straight out of the container. Use serving size charts and measuring glasses instead.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">5) Eat mindfully.</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Mindful eating, which entails be completely aware of why, how, when, where, and what one eats, has many positive effects.&nbsp;<br>Having a better understanding of the body and its needs has a direct impact in making healthy diet choices.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">6) Stimulus and cue control.</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Various societal and environmental signals could induce unnecessary eating. For instance, some individuals tend to overeat when watching television.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">7) Think ahead.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Most effective weight reduction usually occurs when a kitchen those are planned and stocked with foods that are suitable for diets and meal plans.&nbsp;<br>People who want to lose weight or keep it off should get rid of any processed or unhealthy foods from their kitchen and make sure they have the necessary components on hand.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">8) Seek social support.</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">While some people might like to utilise social media to update others on their progress, others might prefer to invite friends or family to join them.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Additional sources of assistance could be:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px; text-align: justify;\">- An encouraging social network<br>- Individual or group therapy<br>- Workout groups or partners<br>- Workplace help programs for employees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">9) Stay positive.</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Weight loss is indeed a gradual process, so if the numbers do not come off as quickly as you had hoped don&rsquo;t get disheartened. Stay Positive.<br>When following a weight loss or maintenance programme, some days will be more difficult than others. In order to lose weight successfully, one must be persistent and refuse to give up when making changes in oneself appears impossible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">10) Exercise Regularly.</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is advised to aim for a minimum of 150 minutes per week if one hour per day is not feasible.&nbsp;<br>This strategy is the greatest long-term technique to guarantee that regular exercise turns into a way of life for them.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Overview</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There is no &ldquo;holiday&rdquo; from leading a healthy lifestyle, which is necessary to maintain weight loss. People should not feel guilty about enjoying a special meal out, a birthday party, or a joyous holiday feast, but they should aim to stay on the path of regular physical exercise and healthy eating.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When people make long-term lifestyle adjustments, it is possible to lose weight and keep it off.</p>', '2023-01-28 19:31:52', 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'weight loss, WEIGHT LOSS Tips, loose weight', 'weight loss, WEIGHT LOSS Tips, loose weight', 1),
(44, 13, 22, 'The Future of Healthcare: The Rise of Telemedicine Adoption', 'Proceed.Fit', 'uploads/1675089417banner_image1.png', 'uploads/1675089417banner_image.png', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The COVID-19 pandemic has accelerated the adoption of telemedicine as patients seek ways to access healthcare without risking in-person visits. Virtual consultations have become a mega trend and is expected to continue to grow even after the pandemic has subsided. As healthcare providers increasingly offer telemedicine services, patients can now receive quality medical care from the comfort and safety of their own homes. The pandemic has emphasized the need for contactless healthcare solutions, and telemedicine has emerged as a game-changer in the medical industry.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Let&rsquo;s understand what Telemedicine is first,</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The use of telecommunication technology for remote diagnosis and treatment of patients is called Telemedicine. It does not require direct contact between the healthcare provider and the patient. All you need a telecommunication media and good internet.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What enables the proper functioning of Telemedicine?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are various components and channels that ensure a seamless telemedicine experience. Some of the components are:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px; text-align: justify;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Computer or mobile phone<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Cameras<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Audio and / or Video conferencing<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Internet</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Telemedicine has eliminated the barrier of distance in healthcare. With virtual consultations, healthcare providers can treat patients in remote or distant locations without the need for in-person visits or face-to-face interactions.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Types of Telemedicine</h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Telemedicine is of various types. Some of them are:</h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Real-time medicine </strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Also known as &ldquo;live medicine&rdquo; which makes the treatment real-time basis. It enables easy interaction between the doctor and patient anytime and anywhere. It is a type of two-way communication process possible through video-conferencing or phone consultations.<br>This makes the consultation and treatment real-time. Various medical practices that are possible with the help of telemedicine are:<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;psychiatric evaluations<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Assessments of medical history<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Basic visual examinations<br>o &nbsp; &nbsp;Ophthalmic tests<br>It uses real-time data to make evaluations of patient health. Data can be sent via telecommunication media. It improves doctors&rsquo; and patients&rsquo; engagement timely, safe, and secure.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Remote patient monitoring</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Remote monitoring is a buzz these days as it has made even a thousand-kilometer distance almost negligible. Patients can reach their doctors without even stepping out of their houses. It really helps in saving a lot of time both for the patient and the doctor.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It has come of great help in times of pandemic. You don&rsquo;t have to worry about getting in contact with another person for treatment. Treatment of various chronic diseases like heart disease, diabetes, and asthma is even possible with the help of remote patient monitoring.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Technology has made it possible to share health-related data with your healthcare service providers through the internet.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Telemedicine has improved the communication process between medical team members. The specialist can get in contact with other physicians and specialists very easily without visiting them in person.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Medical imaging</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Telemedicine also focuses on radiology and other diagnostic specialties. Technology is playing a major role in the transfer and distribution of various medical images, x-rays and CT scans from one expert to another. It enables instant transmission of such data from point of capture to the medical service provider.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It has been of great help when an expert&rsquo;s opinion is needed. You can get an opinion even when the expert is miles away from you.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">How telemedicine helps in reaching patients?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Telemedicine is the new face of healthcare services. On account of telemedicine, medical services experts have different ways of associating with patients in their own homes. Various web-based features like patient portals permit suppliers to share essential data and answer basic inquiries.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Patient portals can be utilized to suggest health-centered mobile apps or instructive materials, like articles and recordings related to health conditions and possible treatments. Patients might try and associate with doctors in virtual visits, and face-to-face interactions from their own houses.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Telemedicine is coming with dramatic improvements in delivering medical assistance to patients.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What all advantages can an increased adoption of telemedicine can bring?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Some of the advantages associated are:<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Better monitoring without personal contacts<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Prevention of exposure to infected patients<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Increased remote healthcare facilities to those sitting in distant places<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Disaster management solutions<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Improved communication between patient and medical service provider<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Time-saving&nbsp;<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Cost-effective method cutting down on commuting cost<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Flexible working hours for experts<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Effective and efficient expert opinion<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Proper data management<br>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Easy follow-ups on patients</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Telemedicine and India</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Telemedicine is evolving in India and soon will be a regular practice too. It is helping in saving cost and time, also making it possible to deal with this pandemic situation. Tele-health service providers are available online and are providing consultations at very affordable prices.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Telemedicine has more to offer than just improving access to healthcare. It also has the potential to drive growth and support the economy. The private sector has taken notice of this potential and is investing in the telemedicine market, looking to capitalize on its benefits. With the rise of remote work and increased demand for virtual healthcare services, telemedicine has become an attractive opportunity for businesses to not only provide valuable services to customers but also generate revenue and create jobs. As technology continues to advance, the market for telemedicine is expected to grow, further supporting economic growth and creating new opportunities in the healthcare industry.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In conclusion, the rise of telemedicine has revolutionized the healthcare industry and has brought a lot of benefits to both patients and healthcare providers. With telemedicine, patients no longer have to travel long distances to receive medical treatment and can easily connect with their healthcare provider from the comfort of their own homes. Additionally, telemedicine has proven to be a cost-effective solution and has greatly reduced the burden on traditional healthcare systems. Furthermore, the private sector has also seen the potential in telemedicine and has invested in the field, leading to increased growth and development. Overall, telemedicine has brought about a new era in the healthcare industry and is set to continue growing in the future.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Note : The information provided here is for general informational purposes only and is not intended to be a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. If you have any concerns about your health or are experiencing symptoms, it is important to consult with a healthcare professional. They will be able to assess your specific situation and provide you with personalised advice and treatment based on your symptoms, body type, allergies (if any), existing medical conditions etc.&nbsp;It is always a good idea to consult with a healthcare professional before making any decisions about your health.</span></p>', '2023-02-09 09:17:41', 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'telemedicine, future of healthcare, future of medicine, healthcare', 'telemedicine,future of healthcare,future of medicine,healthcare,future of health,the future of care,is telemedicine the future,future of ai,college of medicine,disadvantages of telehealth nursing,history of telehealth nursing,yale school of medicine,american association of medical colleges,pros and cons of telehealth nursing,coordination of care,digital healthcare research,telemedicine options,telehealth nursing practice scope & standards of practice', 1),
