(113, 'Dementia', 0, '2023-03-31 08:12:05', 1, '1', NULL, 'A set of symptoms that substantially impair memory, reasoning, social skills, and when they significantly interfere with day-to-day functioning are referred to be dementia. Although there isn\'t one particular illness that causes dementia, many illnesses can. Memory loss is a common symptom of dementia. There are various possible causes of dementia. Poor blood flow, aberrant protein buildup, and degenerative changes in the brain are just a few of them. Simple symptoms like forgetting crucial dates or events might develop into more severe ones like forgetting to put on clothing or eat on time as the condition worsens. Dementia is a progressive mental condition and can worsen with time. Symptoms of dimentia can be suppressed by medications but one can\'t treat it completely.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
