(138, 'Eczema', 0, '2023-03-31 08:12:05', 1, '1', NULL, 'Eczema is a widespread chronic skin illness characterised by skin areas that are dry, extremely itchy, and irritated. Although there are other varieties of eczema, the word \"eczema\" typically refers to the condition known as \"atopic dermatitis,\" which is the most common variety. An interaction between environmental and genetic disturbance leads to atopic dermatitis. In most cases eczema symptoms are mild. The most common symptoms of eczema include dry, scaly skin, skin flushing, itching, open, crusted, or weeping sores. Eczema can last a lifetime, and patients frequently have long stretches of symptom-free remission followed by brief but severe flare-ups. However, by maintaining healthy, moisturised skin, symptoms can be avoided and controlled at home with care and solutions. Corticosteroid creams can be used as a treatment for eczema as they\'re good ailment to allergies. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
