(46, 17, 'What is Appendix?', 'A. Appendix is a blind-ended tube connected to a pouch-like structure i.e. cecum. It develops from the cecum embryologically. The cecum is a structure of the colon which is located at the junction of both intestines (small and large)', '2022-12-15 15:20:49'),
(47, 17, 'In which part of the body is Appendix located?', 'The appendix is located at the junction of the small intestine and large intestine. It is a thin tube of approximately four-inch lengths. Generally, the appendix is placed in the lower right-hand side of the abdomen. Appendicitis pain may be initiated in the middle part of the abdomen.', '2022-12-15 15:22:42'),
(48, 17, 'Is there a difference Appendicitis and Appendix differ?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">A. The appendix is an external body or an outgrowth part. It is a small, worm-like attached to the colon. When the appendix gets blocked, Appendicitis occurs.</span></p>\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Appendicitis is an inflammation of the appendix, a pouch-shaped organ connected to the large intestine. Without treatment, the appendix can rupture. This can lead to life-threatening situations. It is recommended to seek medical advice if there are possible symptoms of Appendicitis.</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-12-15 15:22:51'),
(49, 17, 'What are the visible symptoms of Appendicitis?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">A. The most prominent and common symptoms and signs which are seen in children and adults of Appendicitis are enlisted below.</span></p>\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Loss of appetite</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Pain around the belly button</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Abdominal pain (lower right side)</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Nausea and vomiting</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Abdominal tenderness</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Fever</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Diarrhoea</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Constipation</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">In Children under age group 2 below symptoms are seen:</span></p>\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Vomiting</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Abdominal bloating or swelling</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Tender abdomen</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Older children and teenagers may show the following symptoms:</span></p>\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Pain in the lower right side of the abdomen</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Nausea</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Vomiting</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-12-15 15:23:01'),
(50, 17, 'What are the causes of Appendicitis?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">A. In most cases causes of appendicitis cannot be identified. appendicitis occurs due to many reasons. An obstruction in the appendix may lead to appendicitis. Partial and complete obstruction; can be responsible for the occurrence of appendicitis. An accumulation of faecal matter may lead to obstruction. The other possible reasons behind the obstruction can be:</span></p>\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Tumours</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Worms</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Enlarged lymphoid follicles</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Trauma</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">There are chances of multiplication of bacteria inside the organs surrounding the colon when there is an obstruction in the appendix. This enhances the formation of pus which puts additional pressure and it can be painful. As a result of this process, local blood vessels get compressed and there can be the generation of gangrene due to a lack of blood flow to the appendix. A medical emergency may arise if the appendix rupture takes place and faecal matter can fill the abdomen.</span></p>', '2022-12-15 15:23:10'),
(51, 17, 'What are the various methods used is diagnosing Appendix?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">A. After physical examination, the physician may ask for detailed symptoms to determine the presence of appendicitis. Diagnostic tests which be performed for the detection of appendicitis are as below:</span></p>\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Abdominal X-ray</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Barium enema</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Blood tests to confirm the signs of an infection</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://www.medifee.com/tests/urine-routine-test-cost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Urine tests</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">&nbsp;for checking the signs of a UTI or a kidney stone</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://www.medifee.com/tests/sonography-cost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Abdominal ultrasound</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">&nbsp;or&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://www.medifee.com/tests/ct-scan-cost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">CT scan</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">&nbsp;to find the presence of inflammation of the appendix</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://www.medifee.com/treatment/laparoscopic-surgery-cost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Laparoscopy</span></a></span></li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-12-15 15:24:09'),
(52, 17, 'Why diagnosis of Appendicitis is difficult?', '<p>A. Diagnosis of appendicitis is difficult since the position of the appendix in the abdomen may vary. The location of the appendix is at the lower right side of the abdomen most of the time. Appendix gets attached to the other structures in the abdomen through a sheet-like membrane structure called the mesentery. A larger mesentery allows the appendix to move around and as a result of this, the appendix keeps moving down to the other organs such as the pelvis and colon. Hence, inflammation of the appendix looks like the inflammation of other organs. Diagnosis of appendicitis can also be hard to identify when inflammatory problems look similar to it. Right-side diverticulitis is an example of it. Hence patients with the possibility of appendicitis are kept under observation to know the difference between appendicitis and other conditions.</p>', '2022-12-15 09:14:17'),
(53, 17, 'What is Stump Appendicitis?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">A. Post operation, there is a possibility that a small portion of the appendix may remain behind. There are chances of inflammation of this remaining piece of the appendix and it can lead to further complications of appendicitis. Hence, it is possible to observe the recurrence of appendicitis in the case of patients who have previously undergone appendicitis surgery. Stump appendicitis is an acute inflammation of the residual appendix which mostly occurs after laparoscopic appendectomy. It results from obstruction of the lumen of the appendix which is left behind post-surgery in some cases. Since there is the possibility of rupture of the stump as a result of insufficient diagnosis and treatment, early diagnosis is recommended.</span></p>', '2022-12-15 15:24:17'),
(54, 17, 'What treatments are available for Appendicitis?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">A. Based on the diagnosis, the need for surgery is decided. Antibiotics are recommended before the surgery in most cases. Medication helps prevent post-operative infections. Appendectomy is the surgical removal of the appendix. Based on the severity of appendicitis, an open appendectomy or a laparoscopic appendectomy is performed.</span></p>', '2022-12-15 15:24:27'),
(55, 17, 'What is an Open Appendectomy?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">A. In open appendectomy an incision is made in the lower right side of the abdomen by the surgeon. The appendix is removed and the wound is closed with the aid of stitches. During this process, the abdominal cavity can be cleaned in case of an appendix burst inside the abdomen.</span></p>', '2022-12-15 15:24:34'),
(56, 17, 'What is Laparoscopic Appendectomy?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">A. As the name indicates, this surgery involves the use of a laparoscope. A few small incisions are made in the abdomen and a laparoscope is inserted into these incisions during the surgery. A laparoscope is a long and thin tube with a camera on the front side. Images of the abdominal area can be displayed on the screen which helps in observing the abdomen and performing surgery using the instruments. Once the appendix is found, it is tied with the aid of stitches and then discarded. After this, dressing and cleaning processes are performed.</span></p>', '2022-12-15 15:24:43'),
(57, 17, 'How Appendicitis can be prevented?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">A. Appendicitis cannot be prevented, but there are some precautions and steps which can be followed to reduce its risk. There is less frequency of occurrence of appendicitis in people with high-fibre diets. A healthy diet containing fresh vegetables and fruits helps increase fibre intake. Timely medical advice is recommended since untreated appendicitis can lead to a medical emergency.</span></p>', '2022-12-15 15:24:50'),
(58, 17, 'What are the complications of Appendicitis?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">A. The most frequently generated complication of appendicitis is perforation. It leads to a Peri-appendiceal abscess which is a collection of infected pus. This occurs due to delays in the diagnosis and treatment of appendicitis. If there is no improvement after the use of antibiotics in patients with appendicitis, surgical treatment needs to be initiated without delay to avoid further complications.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">A very common complication of appendicitis is obstruction or blockage of the intestine. Compression of the intestine because of the inflammation surrounding the appendix causes blockage. This blockage restricts the passage of intestinal contents. If the intestinal area above the blockage gets filled with liquid and gas, swelling of the abdomen takes place and further results in nausea and vomiting. Therefore, it becomes necessary to remove the contents of the intestine using a tube passed through the oesophagus and nose and into the stomach and intestine.</span></p>', '2022-12-15 15:24:57'),
(59, 17, 'Which conditions can mimic Appendicitis?', '<p>A. Below are some conditions that can mimic appendicitis even when it is not present.</p>\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n<li>Meckel\'s diverticulitis</li>\r\n<li>Pelvic inflammatory disease (PID)</li>\r\n<li>Inflammatory diseases of the right upper abdomen</li>\r\n<li>Right-sided diverticulitis</li>\r\n<li>Kidney diseases</li>\r\n<li>Ectopic pregnancy</li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-12-15 09:37:22'),
(60, 2, 'What is Abdominal Aortic Aneurysm ?', '<p>An <strong>abdominal aortic aneurysm (AAA)</strong> is a balloon-like bulge that forms in the aorta, the main artery that carries blood from the heart to the rest of the body. The aorta runs through the abdomen, so an AAA occurs in the part of the aorta that is in the abdomen.</p>\r\n<p>The walls of the aorta are normally thick and strong, but over time, they can become weak and stretch. This can cause the aorta to form an aneurysm, which is a weak or thin spot that bulges outwards. If the aneurysm becomes large enough, it can rupture, which can be life-threatening.</p>', '2022-12-19 07:46:40'),
(61, 2, ' What are the major causes of Abdominal Aortic Aneurysm (AAA)?', '<p>There are several factors that can increase the risk of developing an abdominal aortic aneurysm (AAA).</p>\r\n<h3>Some of the most common causes include:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Aging: The risk of AAA increases with age, and it is most common in people over the age of 60.</li>\r\n<li>Smoking: Smoking is a major risk factor for AAA, as it damages the walls of the aorta and increases the risk of aneurysm formation.</li>\r\n<li>High blood pressure: High blood pressure can put extra strain on the walls of the aorta, making them more likely to become weak and form an aneurysm.</li>\r\n<li>Atherosclerosis: This is a condition in which plaque builds up in the arteries, making them narrow and hard. This can cause an aneurysm to form in the aorta.</li>\r\n<li>Family history: If you have a family history of AAA, you may be more likely to develop an aneurysm yourself.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Men are more likely to develop an AAA than women.</p>\r\n<p>It\'s important to note that not all AAAs have a clear cause, and in some cases, the exact cause may not be known. If you are concerned about your risk for AAA, it\'s important to talk to your doctor about your specific risk factors and what you can do to reduce your risk.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2022-12-19 07:48:45'),
(62, 2, ' What are the symptoms of Abdominal Aortic Aneurysm ?', '<h3>Symptoms of an abdominal aortic aneurysm (AAA) may include:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Abdominal or back pain: Some people with an AAA may experience pain in the abdomen or back, often described as a constant, dull ache.</li>\r\n<li>A pulsating feeling in the abdomen: Some people may feel a pulsating sensation in their abdomen, similar to a heartbeat.</li>\r\n<li>A lump in the abdomen: An AAA may cause a visible bulge in the abdomen.</li>\r\n<li>Other symptoms: Some people with an AAA may also experience shortness of breath, dizziness, or fainting.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>It\'s important to note that some people with AAA may not have any symptoms at all. This is why it\'s important to see a doctor if you are at risk for an AAA, as early diagnosis and treatment can help prevent serious complications. If you have any concerns about your risk for AAA, or if you have any of the above symptoms, it\'s important to speak with a healthcare provider.</p>', '2022-12-19 07:50:30'),
(63, 2, 'What is the treatment for Abdominal Aortic Aneurysm ?', '<p>The treatment for an abdominal aortic aneurysm (AAA) will depend on the size and location of the aneurysm, as well as the overall health of the person affected.</p>\r\n<h3>Some common treatment options include:</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Medication:</strong> For small or medium-sized aneurysms that are not causing symptoms, a doctor may recommend taking medication to control blood pressure and reduce the risk of rupture.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Surgery:</strong> For larger aneurysms or for those that are causing symptoms, surgery may be necessary. There are several different types of surgical procedures that may be used to repair or remove an AAA, including:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Endovascular aneurysm repair (EVAR):</strong> During this procedure, a small incision is made in the groin, and a special device is inserted through the incision and into the aneurysm. The device helps to support the walls of the aorta and reduce the risk of rupture.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Open surgical repair:</strong> During this procedure, the surgeon makes an incision in the abdomen and surgically repairs or removes the aneurysm.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Watchful waiting:</strong> In some cases, a doctor may recommend \"watchful waiting,\" which involves monitoring the aneurysm with regular imaging tests to see if it is growing. If the aneurysm is not causing symptoms and is not growing, a doctor may recommend waiting to see if surgery is necessary.<br>It\'s important to speak with a healthcare provider about the best treatment option for your specific situation. Treatment for AAA may help prevent serious complications and save lives.</p>', '2022-12-19 07:52:25');
