(95, 1, 'What is a diet consultation?', 'A diet consultation is a one-on-one session with a professional dietitian who assesses your nutritional needs, health goals, and lifestyle factors. The dietitian provides personalized recommendations and guidance to help you improve your diet and achieve your desired health outcomes.', '2023-06-20 12:57:02', 1),
(96, 1, 'How long does a diet consultation typically last? ', 'The duration of a diet consultation can vary depending on your specific needs and goals. Generally, it can range from 30 minutes to an hour. The dietitian will ensure that you have ample time to discuss your concerns, ask questions, and receive comprehensive guidance.', '2023-06-19 17:47:45', 1),
(97, 1, 'How can a dietitian or Nutrionist help me? ', 'A dietitian can help you in various ways. They can assess your current eating habits, provide education about proper nutrition, develop personalized meal plans, offer practical tips for healthy eating, address specific dietary concerns or restrictions, and monitor your progress over time. Their expertise and support can empower you to make positive changes and achieve long-term success in managing your health through nutrition.', '2023-06-19 17:47:45', 1),
(98, 1, 'What should I expect during a diet consultation? ', 'During a diet consultation, the dietitian or nutritionist will ask you questions about your medical history, eating habits, lifestyle, and health goals. They may also conduct measurements such as body weight and composition. Based on the information gathered, the dietitian will develop a customized plan that includes dietary recommendations, portion sizes, meal timing, and possibly supplement suggestions. They will also provide guidance on how to incorporate these changes into your daily routine.', '2023-06-19 17:49:45', 1),
(99, 1, 'Do I need to follow a specific diet plan during the consultation? ', 'The dietitian will create a personalized diet plan based on your individual needs and goals. This plan will be designed to optimize your health and nutrition while considering your preferences, restrictions, and lifestyle. The dietitian will work with you to develop a plan that is practical and sustainable, ensuring that you can maintain healthy eating habits in the long term.', '2023-06-19 17:49:45', 1),
(100, 1, 'Can I ask questions during the consultation? ', 'Absolutely! Your diet consultation is an opportunity for you to ask any questions or express any concerns you may have regarding your diet or health. The dietitian or nutritionist is there to provide you with expert advice, address your queries, and offer guidance based on their knowledge and experience.', '2023-06-19 17:49:45', 1),
(101, 1, 'Can I have follow-up consultations? ', 'No, follow-up consultations are not included in this particular proposal. This proposal is designed as a one-time consultation to provide you with a comprehensive diet plan and guidance. For regular monitoring, adjustments, and follow-up sessions, we recommend selecting a different proposal that specifically includes ongoing support and follow-up consultations. This will ensure that you receive the necessary guidance and assistance for long-term success in achieving your health and nutrition goals.', '2023-06-19 17:49:45', 1),
(102, 1, 'How does this consultation proposal differ from the free auto-generated diet plan tool?', 'This consultation offers a personalized approach tailored to your goals, preferences, and lifestyle. You\'ll receive expert guidance from a professional dietitian who will accurately assess your nutritional needs and provide recommendations. The diet plan is customized based on your food preferences and cultural background, ensuring a realistic and sustainable plan. You\'ll also receive ongoing support, addressing your concerns and providing motivation throughout your journey. This consultation focuses on creating lasting lifestyle changes and educates you about healthy habits and strategies for long-term success. Overall, it provides personalized, expert-guided, and customized support beyond the limitations of a free auto-generated diet plan via diet planner tool.', '2023-06-19 17:49:45', 1),
(103, 180, 'Can I customize the rules of the 21-Day Hard Challenge to fit my lifestyle? ', 'No, the rules of the 21 Day Hard Challenge are intended to be followed exactly as outlined. The challenge is designed to push you outside your comfort zone and test your commitment to personal growth.', '2023-06-20 12:57:29', 1),
(104, 180, 'Can I skip a day or take a break during the 21-Day Hard Challenge? ', 'No, the challenge requires a continuous commitment for 21 consecutive days. Skipping a day or taking a break would mean starting over from day one.', '2023-06-20 12:10:50', 1),
(105, 180, 'What happens if I fail to complete a task or break a rule? ', 'Failing to complete a task or breaking a rule means starting the challenge from day one again. The 21-Day Hard Challenge demands strict adherence to the rules for optimal results.', '2023-06-20 12:10:50', 1),
(106, 180, 'Can I choose my own workouts for the exercise sessions? ', 'Yes, you have the flexibility to choose the type of workouts that suit your fitness level and preferences. The key is to ensure each session is a minimum of 45 minutes and contributes to your physical fitness.', '2023-06-20 12:10:50', 1),
(107, 180, 'Do I need to follow a specific diet plan during the challenge? ', 'There is no specific diet plan prescribed for the 21-Day Hard Challenge. However, it is recommended to follow a healthy and balanced diet that aligns with your fitness goals and supports your overall well-being.', '2023-06-20 12:10:50', 1),
(108, 180, 'Can I continue the challenge beyond the initial 21 days? ', 'Absolutely! Completing the 21-Day Hard Challenge can be a transformative experience. Many participants choose to continue with their newfound habits and discipline even after the initial challenge period', '2023-06-20 12:10:50', 1),
(109, 180, 'Is the 21-Day Hard Challenge suitable for everyone? ', 'The 21-Day Hard Challenge is a demanding program that requires commitment and discipline. It is recommended to consult with a healthcare professional before starting the challenge, especially if you have any underlying health conditions or concerns', '2023-06-20 12:10:50', 1),
(110, 180, 'Can I participate in the 21-Day Hard Challenge with a partner or as part of a group? ', 'Yes, participating in the challenge with a partner or as part of a group can provide additional motivation and support. However, each individual\'s progress and adherence to the rules will be assessed individually.\r\nRemember, the 21-Day Hard Challenge is a personal journey aimed at pushing your limits and fostering self-improvement. It requires dedication, resilience, and a strong mindset.\r\n', '2023-06-20 12:10:50', 1),
